commit.message: [docs] Everything has moved from docs.mikeboers.com to pyav.org.
[docs] Update Gitter URL.
[docs] Update a few references to the old GitHub repo.
[docs] update the location of the github repository
[build] update URL for FFmpeg binary builds
Remove support for Python 2 buffer protocol.
Bump to next dev version.
Release v8.0.1
[docs] Document FFmpeg features for binary wheels (fixes: #641)

Remove some references to Python 2

Also simplify the `dict_to_avdict` signature as we:

- always pass `clear=True`
- always explicitly pass the `encoding` and `errors` arguments

[build] update FFmpeg build with additional libraries

The following were added:

- libaom
- libass
- libbluray
- libdav1d
- libwavpack
- libxvid

Use os.fsencode for both input and output file names (fixes: #600)

It's safe to call os.fsencode() regardless of whether the filename was
passed as `bytes` or `str`. Remove shim for `os.fsencode()`, it has been
available since Python 3.2.
Bump to next dev version.
Release v8.0.0.
[build] produce source distribution tarball
[build] produce binary wheels for Linux / Mac / Windows
[build] use checkout@v2 github action
Bump version to 8.0.0, drop support for Python 2 and 3.4

[build] disable macos tests for now

On OS X, the `ssl` module has an issue which breaks the build.
Strip ICC profile from logos. #622
Import ABC's from collections.abc (fixes: #616)
